text.section:
A domestic animal that is impounded by an animal control unit may not be sold, placed, or destroyed until the animal has been carefully inspected for a tag, tattoo, or other identification to ascertain the owner and:
72 hours have elapsed after notice has been given to the owner;
if the owner cannot be notified, 72 hours have elapsed after the animal is impounded;
the animal is seriously diseased or severely injured; or
the animal is under 3 months of age.
